{
  "doc_id": "35842",
  "text": "CA153 is shown to be highly sensitive for distant metastases, especially in the bone and liver [CITATION_1] . At present, it is recognized as a breast cancer tumor marker, which can be used as an effective indicator for the prognosis of bone metastasis in breast cancer [CITATION_2] . The results of our study indicated that abnormal high CA153 level significantly increased the risk of bone metastases in breast cancer. And the cut-off value of it was 23.25 U/ml in the present study, which was reported to be ranged from 22 to 60 u/ml in previous studies [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . In line with Wojtacki et al. study [CITATION_5] , the sensitivity of CA153 for diagnosing bone metastases in our study was 76.62%, and the specificity of it was 86.97%.",
